      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Even a single glass of wine can trigger a reaction when combined with metronidazole. It's not just about the quantity, but the presence of alcohol at all. The medication's interaction with alcohol is not limited to large amounts; even a small amount can cause discomfort and potentially hinder the effectiveness of the antibiotic. It's best to abstain from alcohol during your treatment to avoid any unpleasant side effects and ensure your recovery. Your health is more important than a single sip of wine.",
      "source": "target",
